<article id="f3a1927d-b2cb-46c0-9ebd-e92bbd69165b" class="page sans"><header><h1 class="page-title">The Capabilities Tech Tree</h1></header><div class="page-body"><h1 id="7ed1d3da-ae57-41ab-aeb7-3bd2bb3a64cb" class="">Startup (levels 0-2)</h1><p id="3535d475-649e-4427-94b8-949f1f1115b3" class="">As a Horizon 3 business, the startup must cement itself in the market by <strong>rapidly evolving the product</strong> so that it can meet its growth objectives. </p><ul id="2c79ff03-c6ba-416a-addb-9e0a3b944f32" class="bulleted-list"><li style="list-style-type:disc">single “team”</li></ul><h1 id="b1a77c49-0787-4dae-b026-f4f7c00c3527" class="">Pre-IPO (levels 3-5)</h1><p id="1b2edc4e-8b23-48ed-91bf-19cbbb8364c6" class="">As a Horizon 2 business, before a company may IPO, there are several technology COMPLIANCE programs to implement, including SOX (1 or 2), and PCI. </p><ul id="e98f8f88-bffc-4599-b28e-d4ad6f2a4d41" class="bulleted-list"><li style="list-style-type:disc">Multiple teams</li></ul><h1 id="195dc708-b27f-4160-b9ae-446ebd3de303" class="">Enterprise (levels 6-8)</h1><p id="cd97fcc5-8ab5-402b-9af7-a28d801669a3" class="">By the time a company has Divisions, it is important to SAFEGUARD production of the main line of business, while still permitting agility to Horizon 3 and Horizon 2 efforts.</p><ul id="eef98e0d-e6ec-4245-a892-db4236c6de6d" class="bulleted-list"><li style="list-style-type:disc">multiple organizations</li></ul><p id="2093e5b7-f9bf-46f4-ab00-03d2ddc6e80c" class="">
</p><h1 id="da7072c2-49d4-445a-9e3b-2b480de2e899" class="">Software Delivery Performance</h1><p id="beb7121c-4ec9-4f53-ad52-f19aeaa43915" class="">Automate testing and deploying changes so that developers can <strong>focus on feature development</strong>.</p><h2 id="24a1004d-1b76-4dff-b049-652d28182831" class="">Deployments</h2><p id="5522e0d2-6d5a-4b87-9ece-e7b3a0d2433f" class="">
</p><ul id="b72ed13f-ca1b-4a1b-8811-11bd32cedfe8" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy0: Deploy manually using an undocumented process</span></li></ul><ul id="572e81c6-bc79-4865-b0c3-870341b9b86d" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy1: Deploy manually using a checklist / script / Makefile</span></li></ul><ul id="15403526-8586-4a24-8819-a5bb173f7c5c" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy2: Deploy automatically after merging to <code>main</code></span></li></ul><ul id="04c80627-b611-47cc-b92c-5220486d8441" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy3: Canary deployments</span></li></ul><ul id="14bab71b-66e5-4c09-8bd5-be86d9cca7bd" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy4: Blue / Green deployments.</span></li></ul><ul id="e3ff121d-2017-460e-a6d6-92eb32d43892" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy4a: Binary Feature Flags with Continual Deployments</span></li></ul><ul id="f5451a3f-91f7-4335-b5ea-fe84df4e56dc" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy5: Single Region Incremental Deployments</span></li></ul><ul id="caf1e78a-f75c-4564-a1d9-a28c0b9860c4" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy5a: Attribute based Feature Flagging </span></li></ul><ul id="c3327a87-a270-40af-87e7-a07f5226c705" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy6: Incremental Deployments to several regions. </span></li></ul><ul id="a97d3b4a-ea42-417c-809d-f2f2821c9267" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Deploy7+: As business needs dictate.</span></li></ul><h3 id="cf573860-d520-4093-bbe1-6df5fb6bb895" class="">Quality Gates</h3><p id="c2471f33-d4dd-4786-87de-f5c50df436e5" class="">Quality gates interrupt proceeding to the next environment until the criteria are met.</p><ul id="ad0db2c5-2f19-48d8-a8da-7ad45780d1bc" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Gate0: Manually check the environments using an undocumented process</span></li></ul><ul id="c555d5da-d2fc-410e-818b-e717a6960b64" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Gate1: Manually check the environments using a checklist before proceeding</span></li></ul><ul id="702d7e47-8be9-45f8-b881-592dab79ff2e" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Gate2: Check the environment using a simple end to end testing suite that represents the “happy path”</span></li></ul><ul id="e23947c8-8087-4b34-ac03-a263d505924f" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Gate3: End to End testing is used to automatically approve deployments</span></li></ul><ul id="ba1c8a50-b59f-44de-a223-66b91c355b1d" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Gate4: Synthetic tests (or similar) are used as an additional quality gate</span></li></ul><h1 id="cd78d693-61d0-488f-9441-bf7bad153a40" class="">Reliability Engineering</h1><h2 id="09de80f4-cdc0-4531-a554-14aeb217acd7" class="">Site Metrics</h2><ul id="61a7d60a-4567-4296-b6f6-adec0062d05b" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Metrics0: Application errors are surfaced through logs and exit();</span></li></ul><ul id="56cceced-1073-4f03-a93f-f4350cc9f50c" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Metrics1: Application errors are sent to Sentry. Performance metrics are sent to DataDog</span></li></ul><ul id="2c886261-2c32-43ac-9c80-acf44d220897" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Metrics2:Troubleshooting dashboard created in DataDog. ← Full stack metrics are sent to DataDog (network, Runtime, OS and cloud, backends)</span></li></ul><ul id="80162aa4-4e02-44ec-9e79-a78d48cd02a5" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Metrics3+: Repeat per team</span></li></ul><ul id="0a3bd57c-337a-489a-a880-e0d6081f1888" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Metrics6+: As business needs dictate.</span></li></ul><p id="19e2bab9-dacf-47bd-a433-812f354a0bd4" class="">
</p><h2 id="11126123-fc03-42a9-befb-28e078b90c80" class="">Logs</h2><ul id="3bd12421-b2dc-4430-aefa-b4647c3fb051" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Logs0: Logs are examined per instance</span></li></ul><ul id="5bc0dc1d-aa1e-4b08-b6e3-a059cb5f4c98" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Logs1: Logs are collected at a single point, S3, CloudWatch, etc..</span></li></ul><ul id="60df72b6-e7f3-4613-8933-cd7a839b1469" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Logs2: Logs are collected for the main site, as well as other systems and can be correlated. For example, DB logs can be interrogated side by side with the main application logs. </span></li></ul><ul id="f8977c87-f82c-42ce-a3e0-e80ca0168393" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Logs3: Logs are shipped to a central metadata collection point, such as DataDog. </span></li></ul><ul id="9db07262-9a10-4e2d-9400-c4a0180a131d" class="to-do-list"><li><div class="checkbox checkbox-off"></div> <span class="to-do-children-unchecked">Logs4+:As business needs dictate.</span></li></ul><p id="fa3bdf82-7416-487c-af98-a8db24faed95" class="">
